Feature: nullfield_variant_boxed — a large (>= 16B) `variant | null` field on the box-in-arena rail

  # `Op`'s largest case `Big` is 24 bytes, so `Holder.f : Op | null` boxes into an 8-byte arena
  # handle (the other side of the size dial from nullfield_variant_plain). Reading a boxed `Big`
  # (10 + 11 + 12 + label 1 = 34) and a boxed `null` (label 8) sums to 42.

  Scenario: box, write, read, and match a large null-union field
    When built and run
    Then exit = 42
